1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,490
Five or six years ago, a very capable professor told me of his plans for writing a book,

2
00:00:05,600 --> 00:00:10,289
a biography of a controversial personality of a few decades ago.

3
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:15,169
His ideas were more than interesting, they were alive, fascinating.

4
00:00:15,360 --> 00:00:20,610
The professor knew what he wanted to say, and he had the skill and energy to say it.

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:27,250
The project was destined to reward him with much inner satisfaction, prestige, and money.

6
00:00:28,320 --> 00:00:35,010
Last spring I saw my friend again, and I innocently asked him whether the book was about finished.

7
00:00:35,200 --> 00:00:36,450
This was a blunder.

8
00:00:36,560 --> 00:00:38,450
It opened up an old wound.

9
00:00:38,880 --> 00:00:40,929
No, he hadn't written the book.

10
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:46,929
He struggled with himself for a moment, as if he were debating with himself whether to explain why.

11
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:50,289
Finally, he explained that he had been too busy.

12
00:00:50,480 --> 00:00:54,610
He had more responsibilities and just couldn't get to it.

13
00:00:55,360 --> 00:01:01,730
In reality, what the professor had done was to bury the idea deep in his mental graveyard.

14
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:04,850
He let his mind grow negative thoughts.

15
00:01:05,120 --> 00:01:10,289
He visualized the tremendous work and sacrifices that would be involved.

16
00:01:10,560 --> 00:01:14,289
He saw all sorts of reasons why the project would fail.

17
00:01:15,280 --> 00:01:18,770
Ideas are important, let's make no mistake about that.

18
00:01:19,040 --> 00:01:22,929
We must have ideas to create and improve anything.

19
00:01:23,280 --> 00:01:26,608
Success shuns the man who lacks ideas.

20
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:30,049
But let's make no mistakes about this point either.

21
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:33,089
Ideas in themselves are not enough.

22
00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:41,329
That idea for getting more business, for simplifying work procedures, is of value only when it is acted upon.

23
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:48,609
Every day, thousands of people bury good ideas because they are afraid to act on them.

24
00:01:48,799 --> 00:01:53,170
And afterward, the ghosts of those ideas come back to haunt them.

25
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:56,450
Put these two thoughts deep in your mind.

26
00:01:56,559 --> 00:02:00,289
First, give your ideas value by acting on them.

27
00:02:00,559 --> 00:02:05,970
Regardless of how good the idea, unless you do something with it, you gain nothing.

28
00:02:07,039 --> 00:02:11,809
Second, act on your ideas and gain mind tranquility.

29
00:02:12,319 --> 00:02:18,530
Someone once said that the saddest words of tongue or pen are these, it might have been.

30
00:02:19,200 --> 00:02:24,770
Every day you hear someone saying something like, had I gone into business seven years ago,

31
00:02:24,880 --> 00:02:27,170
I'd sure be sitting pretty now.

32
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:30,770
Or, I had a hunch it would work out like that.

33
00:02:31,039 --> 00:02:33,329
I wish I had done something about it.

34
00:02:33,760 --> 00:02:39,250
A good idea, if not acted upon, produces terrible psychological pain.

35
00:02:39,440 --> 00:02:44,289
But a good idea acted upon brings enormous mental satisfaction.

36
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,210
Got a good idea?

37
00:02:46,319 --> 00:02:48,289
Then do something about it.

38
00:02:49,520 --> 00:02:53,569
Use action to cure fear and gain confidence.

39
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,410
Here's something to remember.
